{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17507186","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17507186"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:50:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:50:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2609"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2609","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2609"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.04,0.13,0.71,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2609"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97390"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2609","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2609"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2609"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80005"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"456"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2821"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11194"},{"type":"contributions","id":"12678"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33381"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97390","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/97390"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 57-year-old man presents with a three-month history of dull right upper quadrant pain, which has more recently been associated with pain in his right shoulder. His symptoms have started to interfere with his farming work. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He has a 20 pack-year smoking history and drinks two cans of beer a day. He had a holiday in Bali a year ago, but has not had any other overseas travel. On examination, his pulse rate is 80/min, blood pressure 134/92 mmHg and temperature 37.2\u00b0C. The rest of the examination is unremarkable. A CT abdomen is performed and a representative slice shown (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Giant haemangioma","Focal nodular hyperplasia","Amoebic abscess","Hydatid cyst","Hepatoma"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe CT scan shows a multilocular cyst occupying much of the right lobe of the liver. There are areas of calcification in the cyst wall. These are the characteristic appearances of an \u003Cstrong\u003Ehydatid\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Ecyst\u003C/strong\u003E. Whilst this now a relatively uncommon occurrence in Australia, hydatid disease is well recognised in Southeast Asia, the Middle East and parts of America. In Australia it was most typically seen in sheep-farming areas, where sheep and dogs are the usual hosts for the parasite \u003Cem\u003EEchinococcus granulosus. \u003C/em\u003EWith the de-worming of dogs and improved hygiene, hydatid disease is now uncommon in the Australian farming communities - but needs to be considered in migrant populations who have originated in parts of the world where hydatid disease is endemic. These regions include the Middle East and central Asia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECalcification is not a typical feature of \u003Cstrong\u003Ehaemangiomas, focal nodular hyperplasia (FNH) \u003C/strong\u003Eor\u003Cstrong\u003E hepatomas. \u003C/strong\u003EThe predominantly cystic nature would also be atypical for these pathologies. Both hepatoma and FNH are characteristically solid and hypervascular; FNH often with a dense central scar. The lesion is very large and well circumscribed, and in the setting of an \u003Cstrong\u003Eamoebic\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Eabscess\u003C/strong\u003E or other liver abscess the patient would usually be profoundly unwell.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A multilocular cyst with a rim of calcification is characteristic of hydatid disease."],"references":["Higuita NIA, Brunetti E, McCloskey C. Cystic Echinococcosis. J Clin Microbiol. 2016;54:518-23. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26677245/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80005"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2609"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15290"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15290","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15290"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/f939416c-7ab0-4033-9412-68d0bbe99f3d.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/f939416c-7ab0-4033-9412-68d0bbe99f3d.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":497,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80005","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/80005"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-06T15:19:54+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-06T15:19:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2609"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97390"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\u200d\u2620\ufe0f","name":"Radiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedA